This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as it proposes an architecture for an Airborne Network (AN) and develops algorithms for its design and operation. The paper also deals with issues related to connectivity, coverage, and routing in the AN, which are typical concerns in networking research. 

The paper may also belong to the sub-category of cs.IT (Information Theory) as it deals with the transmission range and velocity of the ANPs, which are related to the capacity and reliability of the wireless links in the AN. 

The paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of cs.SY (Systems and Control) as it deals with the control and coordination of the ANPs to maintain the connectivity and coverage of the AN. 

The paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) as it deals with the distributed operation of the ANPs and the routing of data packets in the AN. 

Finally, the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it develops algorithms for optimizing the design and operation of the AN, which can be seen as a complex system that requires intelligent decision-making.
